    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/>Non splendor, non diviti<hi rend="ligature">ae</hi>,
                <lb n="2"/>sed animi corporisque
                <lb n="3"/>hic datur tranquillitas.
            </ab></div>
             
            <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>Particularly notable is the fact that no person is mentioned in the inscription;
                    instead, the sentiment takes center stage.</p>
                <p>The gemination of the l in tranquillitas (line 3) represents a fairly common
                    orthographic deviation in inscriptions (cf. ILS vol. 3, p. 803).</p>
                <p>Interpuncts are used regularly between words, but not at line-ends.</p></div>
            
